data.chText: 经济；经济情况；经济结构
data.enText: the relationship between production, trade and the supply of money in a particular country or region
a market economy (= one in which the price is fixed according to both cost and demand)

data.chText: （就经济体制而言）国家；经济制度
data.enText: a country, when you are thinking about its economic system

data.chText: 在20世纪90年代爱尔兰是西欧经济发展最快的国家之一。
data.enText: Ireland was one of the fastest-growing economies in Western Europe in the 1990s.
the use of the time, money, etc. that is available in a way that avoids waste
We need to make substantial economies.

data.chText: 买便宜衣服实际上划不来。
data.enText: It's a false economy to buy cheap clothes (= it seems cheaper but it is not really since they do not last very long) .
She writes with a great economy of words (= using only the necessary words) .

data.chText: 我们正在家里实行勤俭节约。
data.enText: We're on an economy drive at home (= trying to avoid waste and spend as little money as possible) .
Buy the large economy pack (= the one that gives you better value for money) !
to fly economy (class) (= by the cheapest class of air travel)

simple_means.memory_skill: eco 环境；经济 + nomy …学 → 经济（学）

example: it was a small economy to walk to work every day
there was a saving of 50 cents

tr: frugality in the expenditure of money or resources
example: the Scots are famous for their economy

tr: the system of production and distribution and consumption

value.def: An economy is the system according to which the money, industry, and trade of a country or region are organized.

example.ex: Zimbabwe boasts Africa's most industrialised economy.
example.tran: 津巴布韦是非洲工业化程度最高的经济体。

value.tran: （国家或地区的）经济，经济体制

value.def: A country's economy is the wealth that it gets from business and industry.

example.ex: The Japanese economy grew at an annual rate of more than 10 per cent.
example.tran: 日本经济以年增长率超过10%的速度增长。

value.def: Economy is the use of the minimum amount of money, time, or other resources needed to achieve something, so that nothing is wasted.

example.ex: ...improvements in the fuel economy of cars...
There was mostly silence. I have never known such economy with words.
example.tran: 大部分时候都是沉默，我还从未见过如此惜字如金的情形。

value.def: If you make economies, you try to save money by not spending money on unnecessary things.

example.ex: They will make economies by hiring fewer part-time workers.
example.tran: 他们将通过减少雇用兼职工人来节省开支。

value.def: Economy services such as travel are cheap and have no luxuries or extras.
Economy is used to describe large packs of goods which are cheaper than normal sized packs.

example.tran: 内含150枚各种螺丝的经济装

value.def: If you describe an attempt to save money as a false economy, you mean that you have not saved any money as you will have to spend a lot more later.

example.ex: A cheap bed can be a false economy...
example.tran: 便宜的床看似省钱，其实可能不然。

example.ex: It seems a false economy to me to cut down on libraries.
example.tran: 在我看来，减少图书馆的数量并不是真正的节约。

value.tran: 假节约;看似省钱的做法

trans: 假节约;看似省钱的做法
管制经济(由政府控制国家各项产业并决定产品的种类与数量)
经济舱综合征(在飞机上空间狭窄的经济舱中久坐不动而导致深静脉血栓形成)
混合经济(国有与私营企业并存的经济体系)
小龙经济体(尤指新加坡或韩国等较小的东亚国家或地区飞跃的经济)
